Sameep Tandon - cs184-am
Daiwei Li - cs184-fz

Our code should compile and run on Ubuntu (tested on hive.cs and Daiwei's laptop running 11.04 x64).
The inputs and corresponding notes files are located in the images folder.

cs184-fz submitted the source code

Our ray-sphere intersection code is adapted from
http://wiki.cgsociety.org/index.php/Ray_Sphere_Intersection

Our ray-triangle intersection code follows: http://www.cs.virginia.edu/~gfx/Courses/2003/ImageSynthesis/papers/Acceleration/Fast%20MinimumStorage%20RayTriangle%20Intersection.pdf

Any other code adapted from online or sources are commented within the source code.

Beyond the features in the specification, we have implemented:
- AABB Acceleration using a KD-Tree
- Anti aliasing
- Soft Shadows
- Glossy Surfaces
- Refractions

